A master level course to get overview of ethical issues in theory and practice of public health, also practical skills to analyze cases in public health and to prepare and present research proposal to research ethics committee.Objectives/eesmärkid:  (i) overview of basic issues of the public health ethics and research ethics;  (ii) skills to analyze cases in public health ethics.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1. To know basic theoretical issues of the modern public health ethics and get skills apply to the decision making process.  2. To understand special issues of the public health ethics and their connections to other branches of applied ethics. 3. To acquire the principles of research ethics in public health and preparation project for ethical evaluation by the research ethics committee.
